  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-05 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A mesh-independence verification activity is declared via hasVerificationActivity and is discussed extensively in the validation narrative, but no Evidence node in the package carries a prov:wasGeneratedBy link pointing to that activity, creating a consistency gap (W-CON-05).",
